-- Berjaya Says Kuk, Chu Were Directors of Unit Dissolved in 2000
-- B y   N a t a s h a   K h a n
-- 2012-04-16T12:36:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/berjaya-says-kuk-chu-were-directors-of-unit-dissolved-in-2000.html
Berjaya Corp., the holding company
of Malaysian billionaire Vincent Tan, said Kuk Mong Kong and Chu
Yen Ling were directors of a unit named Syntax that was
dissolved in 2000.  Their role as directors was to advise Berjaya on “proposed
provincial lottery projects in  China ,” according to a  statement 
released today by the Kuala Lumpur-based company.  The company, called Syntax Limited, was incorporated in
 Hong Kong  in October 1992. It was deregistered from the city’s
companies registry and dissolved in December 2000, the statement
said.  “Since the dissolution of Syntax, Berjaya Corporation
Berhad has had no further dealings or association with Madam Kuk
Mong Kong or Mr Chu Yen Ling,” the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natasha Khan in Hong Kong at 
